# Frontend UI rules — LoyaltyApp (Reviews & Social Proof)

## Project basics
- Framework: **Next.js** (App Router), **TypeScript** with `strict` enabled.
- Styling: **Tailwind CSS v4**. Keep UI minimal and accessible.
- Package manager: **pnpm** (workspaces).

## Pages
- `apps/web/app/admin/` — Merchant admin UI, rendered in Shopware admin iframe.
  - Dashboard, Reviews moderation, Settings, GDPR tools.
  - Authenticated via Shopware iframe handshake.
- `apps/web/app/submit-review/[token]/` — Customer review submission page.
  - Standalone page, not embedded in storefront.
  - Token-authenticated (one-time-use).

## File & folder conventions
- `apps/web/components/` — small, reusable UI components.
- `apps/web/hooks/` — React hooks.
- `apps/web/lib/` — utility functions, API client wrapper.

## I18n
- Support English and German.
- Keep translation strings in dedicated files under `apps/web/i18n/`.

## UX & accessibility
- Buttons and forms must have `aria-*` attributes.
- Forms must validate on client side before submission.
- Review submission page must be mobile-friendly.

## Testing
- Unit tests: Vitest + React Testing Library for components.
- Lint: ESLint + Prettier. Run via `pnpm lint`.

## Widget (storefront)
- Widget code lives at `apps/shopware/LoyaltyApp/Resources/app/storefront/`.
- Uses scoped CSS (`.la-widget-*` class prefix) to avoid theme conflicts.
- Injects JSON-LD structured data for SEO.
